<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-43-0578 </DOCNO><TEXT>The basic parameters of the Mesooptical Fourier Transform Microscope (MFTM)for nuclear emulsion, namely, the accuracy of measurements, the resolution,the signal-to-noise ratio, the depth of focus and the speed of operationare treated theoretically. The advantages of the MFTM over the traditionaloptical microscope are presented. 12 refs.; 6 figs.</TEXT></DOC>